The paper deals with multi-frame image super-resolution, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed technique involves designing upscaling filters and shuffling operations, which are related to machine learning (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
